<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Galadan</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-01-20 13:58:36</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>this item is fairly easy to get but requires good faction with the paladins of qeynos. The paladin in qeynos who guards the fishs pool underneath the clerics guild will give you a quest to retrieve the body of a dead fish this can be done in one of 2 ways ( make a mule chr to kill a fish in the pool since the paladin will kos if he sees you do this ) or kill frostbite in the west karanas but be sure the barbarians dont see you do it they will kos you for doing it and you receive severe faction hits for killing frostbite with halas ) once you have a fish body give it back to the paladin and whola a nice magic ring.</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Abby</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-01-22 15:24:50</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Good faction with the Clerics can be obtained by giving Loshun Novashine 3gp to cast heal on you. He is the NPC who is wandering between the Temple of Life, the bar just inside the front gate (forgot the name) and the front gate. He shouts something about ending this strife. It will take a lot of heals to raise your faction. You need at least amiable to complete quest and give the Kaolindl fish to Enic Runkle</font></td></tr></table>
