<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Does killing corrupt guards raise the right faction?</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Spriggan</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-04-20 07:07:40</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>You can also "do" the quest "properly" in the following way (since the reward is for recovering the fish eaten by a Dog, Frostbite, in West Karana):<BR>
<BR>
Go to Surefall Glade, talk to the male druid to the left inside the Druid Guild, he'll give you a flask of Nitrates. Take this to the Zookeeper in Ak'Anon zoo, and he'll make a Regurgitonic. Give this tonic to Frostbite the dog at the Barbarian Village in West Karana, and he spits out the fish. Give the fish to Enic Ruknil and get your reward.<BR>
<BR>
Admittedly, it's much easier for a wizard or a druid, just bind in Qeynos Hills and 'port around.</font></td></tr></table>
